This task involves implementing a more realistic filtering mechanism for identifying players with consistent performance across Strokes Gained categories:

1. **Analyze Current Implementation Issues**:
   - Review the existing coefficient of variation approach that's returning no results
   - Document why the current approach is too strict for real-world golf statistics
   - Identify edge cases where the current filter fails (e.g., when a player has mixed positive/negative values)

2. **Design New Consistency Algorithm**:
   - Implement a standard deviation-based approach to measure consistency across SG categories
   - Set threshold criteria: standard deviation < 1.0 SG units
   - Add additional criteria:
     - No category worse than -2.0 SG
     - Player must have at least one strength > 0 SG
   - Create utility functions to calculate standard deviation across SG categories

3. **Implementation Steps**:
   ```typescript
   // Example implementation of the new consistency filter
   const isConsistentAcrossCategories = (player: Player): boolean => {
     // Extract relevant SG category values
     const sgValues = [
       player.sgPutt,
       player.sgApproach,
       player.sgAroundGreen,
       player.sgOffTee
     ].filter(value => value !== null && value !== undefined);

     // Check if we have enough data
     if (sgValues.length < 3) return false;

     // Calculate standard deviation
     const mean = sgValues.reduce((sum, val) => sum + val, 0) / sgValues.length;
     const squaredDiffs = sgValues.map(val => Math.pow(val - mean, 2));
     const variance = squaredDiffs.reduce((sum, val) => sum + val, 0) / sgValues.length;
     const stdDev = Math.sqrt(variance);

     // Apply criteria
     const hasNoWeakCategory = sgValues.every(val => val >= -2.0);
     const hasOneStrength = sgValues.some(val => val > 0);

     return stdDev < 1.0 && hasNoWeakCategory && hasOneStrength;
   }
   ```

